    "Name": "Scorpion IIC",
    "Details": "Initially produced by the Quikscell Company in 2807, the Scorpion Light Tank is famously easy to repair, available in numbers, and best of all, cheap. Only marginally effective on it's merits, the Scorpion has proven effective in mass numbers. Swarms of Scorpions, easily procured due to their low cost, are an often-encountered danger on poorer worlds. The vehicle is produced on many planets within the Inner Sphere. Many local variations, upgrades, and downgrades as required by circumstance are in use.\n\n<b><color=#ffcc00>Fusion: Expensive engine that works in a Vacuum.</color></b>\n\n<b><color=#ffcc00>Movement: 5/8 Hex: 150/240 Meters.</color></b>\n\n<color=#ffcc00><b>Armor:</b> Armor (C)\n<b>Structure:</b> Structure\n<b>Values       A        S  </b>\n<b>Front</b>       150     15\n<b>Left</b>          80     15\n<b>Right</b>        80     15\n<b>Rear</b>         60     15\n<b>Turret</b>      110     15\n\n<b>Total</b>      480     75</color>\n\n<color=#ff0000>Quirk: Protected Mechanisms</color>",
